        <h2><b>PRIVACY POLICY</b></h2>

        1.General
        <p>Personal data that you provide on the ULCarpooling website will be gathered, used and processed by ULCarpooling project team. This is the responsible party in terms of data protection rights.</p>

        2. Signing up to our website
        <p>To use our online services, you must first sign up to our website with your University of Limerick email address, a username and password. Please protect your password in order to avoid data abuse. On written request, ULCarpooling will be pleased to provide information regarding the data we have stored under your username.</p>

        3. Type, scope and purpose of data use
        <p>The data you provide on signing up will be used for contractually agreed purposes, i.e. for identifying your trip history, allowing use of the website and, if so agreed, for providing other services. We will only use this data for information or promotional purposes if we have your consent to do so. This information is stored electronically.</p>

        4. Third parties
        <p>Your data will be made available to third parties only if ULCarpooling uses the services of those third parties for operating this website and its services. Such a third party could be, for example, a service provider who hosts the website and the data generated along with it. The user explicitly authorizes the forwarding of this data in agreement with our General Terms and Conditions. All third parties who provide services to ULCarpooling are required to comply with relevant data privacy regulations. ULCarpooling may also be legally obliged to forward your data to third parties, such as law enforcement agencies. Beyond the scope described above, your personal data will not be passed on or disclosed to third parties.</p>

        5. Consent/Right of Withdrawal
        <p>Wherever you agree explicitly to a specific use of your data on our website, this agreement will always be voluntary. You are therefore entitled at any time to revoke your consent to the future use of your data.</p>

        6. Cookies, web bugs
        <p>
            Cookies are small text files stored on the hard disks of visitors to our website. Our website is configured to create a session cookie which allows ULCarpooling to offer site services more conveniently. The information stored in cookies makes it easier for you to navigate our website and allows our online pages to be displayed correctly. The information displayed is also customized to your profile. Cookies do not contain personal information.
You can configure your browser to reject cookies, so that they will not be stored on your computer. Please refer to your browserÂ´s instructions for details on how to do this. ULCarpooling does not employ any objects embedded invisibly in the website ("web bugs") for creating statistics about website usage. No personal data is communicated in this fashion.
        </p>

        7. Deleting or blocking personal data
        <p>The data you provided us on signing up to our website will be stored until you cancel your account with us. Your data will then be deleted unless we are under legal obligation to retain it.</p>

        8. Changes to the privacy policy
        <p>ULCarpooling reserves the right to make changes to this privacy policy at any time. ULCarpooling will give you suitable warning should this involve any changes that could be to your detriment.</p>
